  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing emergency health services towards vulnerable returnees and displaced population in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide access to emergency and life-saving health care services - for returnees, IDPs and host communities. This IOM project deploys 3 Mobile Health Teams (MHTs), procures medicines, medical supplies and equipment, provides targeted health education and outreach on COVID-19 and other communicable diseases and provides training to medical staff on outbreak response. The project provides life-saving assistance to 19,000 people, including 19,000 women, 15,000 men, 26,000 children, and 1,200 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
